    <!-- Instructions-->
    <system:String x:Key="Instructions_main" xml:space="preserve">In this menu, you can change some &#xA;settings more advanced than in the &#xA;general settings page since you can edit &#xA;the following :</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Instructions_1" xml:space="preserve">1. Set priority files: Priority files in EasySave &#xA;are the files that will be saved first when &#xA;one or more backup jobs are running. To &#xA;customize the default list, you need to click &#xA;on the extension that you want, and then &#xA;click on the “add” or “Remove” button &#xA;depending on the location of the targeted &#xA;extension and what you want to do with it.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Instructions_2" xml:space="preserve">2. Set the critical threshold, in Kilobytes, of &#xA;file sizes being backed up simultaneously: &#xA;This parameter will define a threshold that &#xA;must not be exceeded to avoid bandwidth &#xA;overload.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Instructions_3" xml:space="preserve">Additional option: Pause running backup &#xA;jobs if the set threshold is exceeded to &#xA;avoid network saturation. You can choose &#xA;to enable or disable this option. If you &#xA;choose to enable it, you have the option to &#xA;select the threshold in Kilobytes.</system:String>

